CRISPRa stim / unstim combined

```{r}

ddsA <- dds[, which(metadata$Type=="a")]
design(ddsA) <- ~1+CRISPR*Stim
ddsA = DESeq(ddsA)

resultsNames(ddsA)

```


```{r}
mod_mat_A <- model.matrix(design(ddsA), colData(ddsA))

# Define coefficient vectors for each condition
wt_unstim_A <- colMeans(mod_mat_A[ddsA$CRISPR == "No" & ddsA$Stim == "No", ])
wt_stim_A <- colMeans(mod_mat_A[ddsA$CRISPR == "No" & ddsA$Stim == "Yes", ])
crispri_unstim_A <- colMeans(mod_mat_A[ddsA$CRISPR == "Yes" & ddsA$Stim == "No", ])
crispri_stim_A <- colMeans(mod_mat_A[ddsA$CRISPR == "Yes" & ddsA$Stim == "Yes", ])

```

```{r}

# CRISPRa Stim
resA_crispr_stim <- results(ddsA, contrast = crispri_stim_A - wt_stim_A)
nrow(resA_crispr_stim[!is.na(resA_crispr_stim$padj) & resA_crispr_stim$padj<0.05,])
resA_crispr_stim_signif = resA_crispr_stim[!is.na(resA_crispr_stim$padj) & resA_crispr_stim$padj<0.05,] 
head(as.data.frame(resA_crispr_stim_signif))
```

```{r}

# CRISPRi Unstim
resA_crispr_unstim <- results(ddsA, contrast = crispri_unstim_A - wt_unstim_A)
nrow(resA_crispr_unstim[!is.na(resA_crispr_unstim$padj) & resA_crispr_unstim$padj<0.05,]) 
resA_crispr_unstim_signif = resA_crispr_unstim[!is.na(resA_crispr_unstim$padj) & resA_crispr_unstim$padj<0.05,] 
head(as.data.frame(resA_crispr_unstim_signif))

```


Now look at CRISPRi - note that expect it to be stronger than in Nora's cells.
I think a joint model for Stim and Unstim should work fine, based on the consistency betweeen joint and separate ones for CRISPRa

